result.execSummary:
The defendant Amy Jean Poling was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Amy Jean Poling is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Amy Jean Poling was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CO: Lundell, RPR: Val Deiss, Clerk: Webb, ADA: Michael Edward Nieskes   DF ATTY:  Alex Andrea   DF:  Amy Jean Poling appeared. Court called.  Set for PTC.  Includes 15CM721, 15CM769, 16CM102, 16CM123, 15TR5377, 15TR5378 & 15TR5590.  There is an agreement.  Attorney Andrea recites the agreement.  DE files a Plea Quesitonnaire and Waiver of Rights Form with the Court.  Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea.  Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads No Contest to Ct 1 in 16CM123 & Ct. 3 in 15CM769 with the Domestic Abuse Enhancer stricken. Crt reviews the police reports Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds the DE adjudciated guilty of Ct 1 in 16CM123 & Ct. 3 in 15CM769 with the Domestic Abuse Enhancer stricken. On motion of the State without objecton, Crt dismisses Ct. 2 & Ct. 3 in 16CM123 & Ct. 1, Ct. 2 & C.t 4 in 15CM769 & dismiss 15CM721, 16CM102, 15TR5377 & 15TR5378. . Sentencing arguments. Crt orders:

C.1  in 16CM123 & Ct. 15CM769 to run concurrent to each other
- S/W 1 year probation with conditions
- Probation can be transferred to Dunn County
- AODA and follow through with any recommended therapy or treatment
- Absolute sobriety:  Zero alcohol, zero controlled substances, zero prescribed medications (except as taken and prescribed for you by a physician) in your system, on your person, or in your possession at all times while this case is ongoing. This prohibition includes drug paraphernalia.
- Court costs waived.  DE ordered to pay $400 for the DNA surcharge
- DE to meet with the payment clerk for a payment plan
- DE to report to probation today 07/28/16
- DE's bail remains in effect until the DE has signed up for probation and then it is vacated
- If revoked the DE has 12 days credit time served
- 20 days to appeal

Court proceeds with sentencing on 15TR5590.  Court questions the DE.  DE enters a No Contest plea on Ct. 1 in 15TR5590.  Court enters a No Contest plea.  Court finds the DE adjudicated guilty of Ct. 1 in 15TR5590. Sentencing arguments.  Crt Orders:

Ct. 1 in 15TR5590
- AODA and follow through with any recommended treatment or therapy and can complete in Dunn County
- 6 months driver's license revocation
- Court orders F/F of $811.50
- DE to meet with the payment clerk for a payment plan
- 20 days to appeal
